children.subject: Thanks for the reply! Would you say 126/162 is manageable or similar to 61c/16b? I know 161/162 would be easier but I’m leaning towards the former right now, provided it’s manageable.

(different anon) 61C isn’t comparable to 162 in terms of workload - there are already plenty of posts on 162 so I’ll leave it at that. I haven’t taken 126, but it’s notorious for its difficulty. So no, 61C + 16B is much, much less work than 126 + 162. 126 + 162 is doable imo, but not easy. 161 is probably more comparable to 61C, with relatively easy assignments, a lot of memorization wtt material, but non-trivial projects.

If you’d still like to do 126, I’d recommend you do some more research on 126 and 162 workloads; there’s plenty of information on this Piazza in older posts. You may want to take something else with 126.
126 and 162 is doable (but a ton of work) if you don't have a lot of other time commitments. If you're a TA or active in a club I wouldn't recommend it.

126 has a fair workload but the material itself is not too bad. Definitely overblown by a lot of people. It has similar weekly problem sets to 70 and adds around 7 jupyter notebook labs in total. The real difficulty is just doing well compared to the curve.

The latter is definitely more manageable, and more useful for generic SWE roles. If you wanted to get into DS/ML-y roles then taking 126/127/189 would be more helpful, but for your run-of-the-mill SWE Intern positions, 160s + 186 appear more useful.
